  m_Name: Character_marra
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.CharacterProfileData
  _id: marra
  _characterName: Marra
  _role: Cook / recipe mentor
  _age: Mid-fifties
  _home: The Crooked Pintle kitchen
  _work: Cooking, recipes, and kitchen orders
  _keepsake: Copper cooking pot
  _tagline: The cook who can make a meal, a lesson, and a warning from one basket.
  _leadParagraph: Marra is Hollowfen's compact force of kitchen authority, with rolled
    sleeves, strong arms, and no patience for careless handling of good ingredients.
  _backgroundParagraph: She turns Wren's first forage into a meal that brings people
    back to the Crooked Pintle, then becomes the village's recipe mentor and most
    exacting buyer.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Marra trusts texture, temperature, and useful work. Gratitude
    comes out as instruction, and hope is something she prefers to serve in a bowl.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: I'll tell you twice and not three times.
  _displayNameId: character.marra.name
  _descriptionId: character.marra.lead
  _sortOrder: 2
  _category: 0
  _edition: 03 / MARRA
  _previewScale: 1
  _tPosePlate: {fileID: 0}
  _characterSheet: {fileID: 0}
  _missions:
  - Act: 1
    QuestId: firstSale
    Title: Marra's Kitchen
    Summary: Inspect Wren's first basket and turn it into a proper meal.
  - Act: 2
    QuestId: edsGrandfather
    Title: Brightspore at the Bedside
    Summary: Prepare the bitter tonic for Edda's grandfather.
  - Act: 2
    QuestId: cottagesReopen
    Title: Two Boards Come Down
    Summary: Prepare for returning households that will need bread.
  - Act: 3
    QuestId: festivalHosted
    Title: The First Festival in Three Years
    Summary: Name and cook the four festival dishes.
  _quotes:
  - Text: You wash these in cold water. Not hot. Hot bruises them and makes liars
      of the texture.
    Context: Teaching Wren how to handle the first basket.
  - Text: I'll tell you twice and not three times.
    Context: Establishing the rules of her kitchen.
  - Text: Four dishes by sundown. If anyone calls it rustic, I will make them eat
      the garnish.
    Context: Opening the festival gathering.
